{"BIACID":[{"def":"Having two hydrogen atoms which can be replaced by negative atoms or radicals to form salts; -- said of bases.","pos":""}],"BIACUMINATE":[{"def":"Having points in two directions.","pos":""}],"BIANGULAR":[{"def":"Having two angles or corners.","pos":""}],"BIANNUAL":[{"def":"Occurring twice a year; half-yearly; semiannual.","pos":""}],"BIANTHERIFEROUS":[{"def":"Having two anthers.","pos":""}],"BIARTICULATE":[{"def":"Having, or consisting of, tow joints.","pos":""}],"BIAS":[{"def":"A weight on the side of the ball used in the game of bowls, or a tendency imparted to the ball, which turns it from a straight line.","pos":""},{"def":"A learning of the mind; propensity or prepossession toward an object or view, not leaving the mind indifferent; bent inclination.","pos":""}],"BIAURICULATE":[{"def":"Having two auricles, as the heart of mammals, birds, and reptiles.","pos":""},{"def":"Having two earlike projections at its base, as a leaf.","pos":""}]}